IAPL/Standard_CarrierA.md.content:
# Specimen Policy: Investment Adviser Professional Liability (IAPL)
**Form Number:** MCA-IAPL-100 (01/24)
**Carrier:** Carrier A
**Form Type:** Industry Standard

The Insurer shall pay, on behalf of each Insured Person, Loss resulting from any Claim first made against such Insured Person during the Policy Period (or the Discovery Period, if applicable) for a Wrongful Act in the performance of or failure to perform Professional Services by such Insured Person, but only when and to the extent that the Company has not indemnified such Insured Person for such Loss.

The Insurer shall pay, on behalf of the Company, Loss resulting from any Claim first made against the Company during the Policy Period (or the Discovery Period, if applicable) for a Wrongful Act in the performance of or failure to perform Professional Services by the Company or by any Insured Person.

The Insurer shall pay, on behalf of the Company, Loss resulting from any Claim first made against an Insured Person during the Policy Period (or the Discovery Period, if applicable) for a Wrongful Act in the performance of or failure to perform Professional Services, but only when and to the extent that the Company has indemnified such Insured Person for such Loss.

The Insurer shall have the right and duty to defend any Claim seeking Loss which is covered by this Policy, even if any or all of the allegations in such Claim are groundless, false, or fraudulent. The Insurers duty to defend shall cease upon exhaustion of the applicable Limit of Liability. The Insurer may, with the written consent of the Insured, settle any Claim as the Insurer deems expedient. If the Insured refuses to consent to a settlement recommended by the Insurer, the Insurers liability for Loss shall not exceed the amount for which the Claim could have been settled plus Defense Costs incurred up to the date of such refusal.
The Insurer shall not be liable for Loss in connection with any Claim:

Based upon, arising out of, or in any way involving any criminal, fraudulent, or malicious act, or any willful violation of statute. This exclusion shall only apply if there is a final, non-appealable adjudication in the underlying proceeding or a separate proceeding establishing such conduct. This exclusion shall not apply to Defense Costs, which shall be advanced until such final adjudication.

Based upon, arising out of, or in any way involving any Insured gaining any profit, remuneration, or financial advantage to which such Insured was not legally entitled. This exclusion shall apply only if there is a final, non-appealable adjudication establishing such advantage.
For bodily injury, sickness, disease, or death of any person, or damage to or destruction of any tangible property.
For any actual or alleged violation of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 (ERISA).

**Endorsement CA-01: Cyber Liability Exclusion (Amended)**
This Policy does not apply to any Claim based upon or arising out of a Cyber Attack or unauthorized access to the Companys computer systems.

**Endorsement CA-02: Sanctions Limitation Clause**
No coverage shall be provided for any Insured who is a Specially Designated National (SDN).

IAPL/Standard_CarrierB.md.content:
# Specimen Policy: Investment Advisory Liability (IAL)
**Form Number:** CB-IAL-2024-V4
**Carrier:** Carrier B
**Form Type:** Industry Standard
The Underwriter will pay on behalf of the Insureds all Loss resulting from a Professional Claim first made against an Insured during the Policy Period for an Advisory Act.

The Underwriter has the right and duty to defend any Professional Claim, even if the allegations are groundless. Defense Costs shall be paid by the Underwriter as part of the Loss and shall erode the Limit of Liability. The Underwriter shall advance covered Defense Costs on a current basis, but no later than 60 days after receipt of itemized invoices.

If a Claim includes both covered and non-covered matters, or is made against both covered and non-covered parties, the Insureds and the Underwriter agree to use their best efforts to determine a fair and reasonable allocation between covered and non-covered Loss. In the absence of an agreement, the Underwriter shall advance Defense Costs on a 100% basis until a final allocation is reached.

**Advisory Act** means any actual or alleged act, error, omission, misstatement, misleading statement, or breach of fiduciary duty committed solely in the rendering of Investment Advisory Services.

**Investment Advisory Services** means services performed for a Client of the Insured Entity for a fee or other compensation, consisting of investment management, financial planning, or investment advice. This definition includes services as a "Robo-Adviser" or automated platform if disclosed in the Application.

**Insureds** means (i) the Insured Entity, and (ii) any Insured Person.

**Insured Person** means any natural person who was, is, or shall be a director, officer, member, partner, or employee of the Insured Entity. Insured Person also includes any "leased employee" while performing duties for the Insured Entity under a written contract.

**Loss** means the total amount the Insureds become legally obligated to pay on account of a Claim, including settlements, judgments, and Defense Costs. Loss specifically includes punitive or exemplary damages where insurable under the law most favorable to the Insured.
The Underwriter shall not be liable for Loss under this Policy on account of any Claim:

Based upon or arising out of any deliberately dishonest or fraudulent act, or the gaining of any profit to which the Insured was not legally entitled. This exclusion only applies if a final judgment or adjudication in a proceeding adverse to the Insured establishes such conduct. This exclusion shall not be imputed to any other natural person Insured.
Based upon or arising out of any Advisory Act or circumstance which has been the subject of any notice given under any other policy of which this Policy is a renewal or replacement.

Based upon or arising out of any liability assumed by an Insured under any contract or agreement, provided that this exclusion shall not apply to liability the Insured would have in the absence of such contract.

**Endorsement CB-V4-08: Cost of Correction (Limited)**
The Underwriter will reimburse the Insured Entity for a Correction Loss incurred to rectify a Trade Error, provided the Trade Error is discovered and reported within 72 hours of its occurrence. Sublimit: $50,000.

**Endorsement CB-V4-12: Amended Insured vs Insured**
Section 3.4 (Insured vs Insured) is deleted in its entirety and replaced with a carve-back for derivative suits brought without the assistance or solicitation of any Insured Person.

IFL/Standard_CarrierA.md.content:
# Specimen Policy: Investment Fund Liability (IFL)
**Form Number:** MCA-IFL-2024-V2
**Carrier:** Carrier A
**Form Type:** Industry Standard

The Insurer shall pay, on behalf of each Individual Insured, Loss resulting from any Claim first made against such Individual Insured during the Policy Period for a Wrongful Act, but only to the extent that the Fund is not required or permitted to indemnify the Individual Insured. **Retention:** $0.

The Insurer shall pay, on behalf of the Fund, Loss resulting from any Claim first made against an Individual Insured during the Policy Period for a Wrongful Act, but only to the extent that the Fund has indemnified such Individual Insured for such Loss.
The Insurer shall pay, on behalf of the Fund, Loss resulting from any Securities Claim first made against the Fund during the Policy Period for a Wrongful Act by the Fund.

The Insurer has the right and duty to defend any Claim seeking covered Loss. The Insurer shall advance Defense Costs on a current basis, subject to a written undertaking from the Insured to repay such costs if it is finally determined that the Loss is not covered.

**Individual Insured** means any natural person who was, is, or shall be:
(1) a Director, Officer, Manager, or equivalent of the Fund or a Subsidiary;
(2) a member of a Funds advisory board or investment committee; or
(3) an Employee of the Fund, but only for a Securities Claim or while acting in a managerial capacity.

**Securities Claim** means a Claim made against any Insured alleging a violation of the Securities Act of 1933, the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, or any state "Blue Sky" law. Securities Claim does not include any Claim brought by a vendor or competitor of the Fund unless such Claim is also brought by a shareholder in their capacity as such.

**Wrongful Act** means:
(1) with respect to an Individual Insured, any actual or alleged act, error, omission, neglect, or breach of duty;
(2) with respect to the Fund, any actual or alleged act, error, or omission in connection with a Securities Claim.

**Loss** includes judgments, settlements, and Defense Costs. Loss also includes "Stockholders' Derivative Demand Investigation Costs" up to a sublimit of $100,000.

The Insurer shall not be liable for Loss on account of any Claim brought by or on behalf of any Insured. **Carve-back:** This exclusion does not apply to:
(i) any Claim brought in a jurisdiction outside the United States;
(ii) any derivative suit brought independently of any Insured; or
(iii) any Claim brought by a former Individual Insured who has not served the Fund for at least 3 years.
Based upon or arising out of any violation of Section 16(b) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (Short-Swing Profits).
Based upon any Wrongful Act occurring before the "Prior Acts Date" of January 1, 2022.

**Endorsement IFL-MCA-05: Amended Pollution Exclusion**
Narrows the exclusion to apply only to the discharge of hazardous waste into the environment, providing a carve-back for derivative suits following a pollution event.

**Endorsement IFL-MCA-12: Spousal Extension**
Extends the definition of Individual Insured to include the lawful spouse or domestic partner of an Individual Insured for Claims seeking Loss from marital property.

IFL/Standard_CarrierB.md.content:
# Specimen Policy: Management and Fund Liability (MFL)
**Form Number:** CB-MFL-2024-V1
**Carrier:** Carrier B
**Form Type:** Industry Standard

The Underwriter will pay on behalf of the Insured Persons all Loss for which the Insured Persons are not indemnified by the Fund and which they are legally obligated to pay on account of a Claim for a Wrongful Act.
The Underwriter will pay on behalf of the Fund all Loss for which the Fund has indemnified the Insured Persons on account of a Claim for a Wrongful Act.
The Underwriter will pay on behalf of the Fund all Loss which the Fund is legally obligated to pay on account of a Claim first made against the Fund for a Wrongful Act by the Fund.

The Underwriter shall have the right and duty to defend any Claim even if false or fraudulent. The Underwriter may settle any Claim if it is in the best interest of the Fund, provided the Funds consent is obtained (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld).

**Fund** means the entity named in the Declarations and any Subsidiary.

**Insured Persons** means all natural persons who were, are, or shall be duly elected or appointed directors, officers, or trustees of the Fund, or their functional equivalent. Coverage also extends to "General Counsel" and "Compliance Officers."

**Wrongful Act** means any actual or alleged act, error, omission, misstatement, misleading statement, or breach of duty committed by an Insured Person in their capacity as such, or by the Fund.

**Loss** includes compensatory damages, statutory multiples, and Defense Costs. Loss does not include (a) taxes, (b) fines or penalties, or (c) the multiple portion of multiplied damages.

The Underwriter shall not be liable for Loss arising from any Insureds fraudulent or criminal act or the gaining of any profit to which the Insured was not legally entitled. This exclusion only applies if established by a "Final Adjudication" in the underlying action.
No coverage for any Claim based upon any litigation or proceeding pending against any Insured as of the "Pending and Prior Date."

Excludes all liability for physical injury to persons or damage to tangible property. **Carve-back:** This exclusion does not apply to "Non-Indemnified Side A" Defense Costs in an action alleging such injury.

**Endorsement CB-MFL-04: Continuity Amendment**
Limits the "Prior Knowledge" application to the Knowledge of the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer only.

**Endorsement CB-MFL-09: Derivative Demand Investigation**
Adds a $50,000 sublimit for reasonable legal fees incurred by the Fund in evaluating a demand by a shareholder to bring a lawsuit.

PEX/Standard_CarrierA.md.content:
# Specimen Policy: Private Equity Management Liability (PEX)
**Form Number:** MCA-PEX-2024-V1
**Carrier:** Carrier A
**Form Type:** Industry Standard

The Insurer shall pay, on behalf of the Insureds, Loss resulting from any Claim for a Wrongful Act in the management of the Private Equity Firm, but only when such Claim is first made during the Policy Period.

The Insurer shall pay, on behalf of the Insured Persons, Loss resulting from a Claim for a Wrongful Act committed while serving at the written request of the Private Equity Firm as a director, officer, or manager of a Portfolio Company. 
*   **Provision:** This coverage is excess of any indemnification or insurance provided by the Portfolio Company.
*   **Sub-clause:** Coverage is limited to those Portfolio Companies disclosed in the Application and Scheduled via Endorsement.

The Insurer has the right and duty to defend any Claim. Defense Costs shall be advanced by the Insurer every 30 days upon receipt of reasonable invoices. Advancement is subject to an undertaking to repay if the Loss is ultimately determined to be non-covered.

**Portfolio Company** means any entity in which the Private Equity Firm, directly or indirectly, holds an equity investment (whether majority or minority).

**Insured** means the Private Equity Firm, any subsidiary, and any Insured Person.

**Insured Person** means:
(1) any General Partner, Managing Member, or Principal of the Private Equity Firm;
(2) any Employee of the Private Equity Firm while acting in a managerial capacity;
(3) any "Outside Director" serving on the board of a Portfolio Company at the Firms request.

**Wrongful Act** means any actual or alleged act, error, omission, or breach of duty committed in the course of (i) Venture Capital or Private Equity activities, or (ii) Investment Advisory Services.
Excludes any Loss arising from a deliberately fraudulent act. This exclusion applies only if established by a "Final, Non-Appealable Adjudication" in the underlying proceeding.

Excludes liability arising from services as a broker, dealer, or investment banker. **Carve-back:** Does not apply to the Firms activities in identifying or negotiating the acquisition of Portfolio Companies.
Absolute exclusion for physical harm. **Exception:** This exclusion does not apply to a Securities Claim resulting from a catastrophic event at a Portfolio Company.

**Endorsement PEX-MCA-01: Run-off for Retired Partners**
Provides an automatic 6-year Discovery Period for any Partner who retires during the Policy Period, specifically for acts committed prior to their retirement date.

**Endorsement PEX-MCA-09: Amended OEL Priority**
Specifies that this Policy is primary to any personal umbrella liability policy held by an Insured Person, but excess to any insurance held by the Portfolio Company.

PEX/Standard_CarrierB.md.content:
# Specimen Policy: General Partner and Portfolio Liability (GPPL)
**Form Number:** CB-GPPL-2024-SPEC-V1
**Carrier:** Carrier B
**Form Type:** Industry Standard
The Underwriter shall pay on behalf of the General Partner all Loss resulting from a Claim for a Wrongful Act by the General Partner or any Insured Person.

The Underwriter shall pay on behalf of an Insured Person all Loss for which such Insured Person is not indemnified by the Portfolio Company, arising from a Claim for a Wrongful Act committed in their capacity as a director of such Portfolio Company.
The Underwriter shall pay on behalf of the Firm all Loss resulting from a Claim first made against the Firm for a Wrongful Act by the Firm in the performance of Private Equity Services.

**Private Equity Services** means the management of one or more Funds, the solicitation of Limited Partners, the selection of Portfolio Companies, and the provision of advice to Portfolio Companies.

**Insured Person** means any natural person who was, is, or shall be:
(a) a Manager, Officer, or Partner of the General Partner;
(b) a member of the Firms Investment Committee;
(c) any "Board Observer" at a Portfolio Company, but only for acts committed in that capacity.

**Portfolio Company** means any corporation, partnership, or other entity in which a Fund (managed by the General Partner) owns an interest.

**Wrongful Act** means any actual or alleged act, error, omission, neglect, or breach of duty.

The Underwriter is not liable for Loss arising from any Insured's dishonest or fraudulent act. This exclusion requires a "Final Adjudication" against the Insured. Severability exists such that the act of one Insured Person is not imputed to any other Insured Person.
Excludes any Loss arising from the receipt of any profit to which the Insured was not legally entitled.
No coverage for (i) the issuance or underwriting of securities for third parties, or (ii) the day-to-day manufacturing, distribution, or retail operations of any Portfolio Company.

**Endorsement CB-GPPL-10: Spousal and Estate Coverage**
Extends the definition of Insured Person to include the estate, heirs, and legal representatives of a deceased or insolvent Insured Person.

**Endorsement CB-GPPL-15: Notice of Acquisition**
New Portfolio Companies are automatically covered if the Fund's investment is <$50M or <25% of the Portfolio Company's total equity.
